Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.89,0:00:10.89,2,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFF00&}听译： 呔    墙头草  {\fn@SimSun-ExtB} Macchiato02  Quixote2010 {\fn新宋体} 时间轴：呔  后期：墙头草
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.89,0:00:16.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,开拍\NAction
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.13,0:00:20.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他对收据的事不依不饶的 非留下我检查一遍系统不可\NHe's demanding that I stay and go over his system
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.56,0:00:26.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我没法推辞 根本走不掉 对 就这样说\NAnd I cannot get out of it,yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.24,0:00:28.33,2,NTP,0,0,0,,现在我们回到了全剧的开头\NWe are going back to the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.46,0:00:31.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是决定后来剧情走向的阶段\NTo a defining era of Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.65,0:00:37.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在全剧完结前 我们想确保讲述一个前后连贯的故事\NBefore the series ended,we wanted to make sure that we had our origin story
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.13,0:00:40.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,确保我们能看到一些没拍的前情细节\NThat we saw everything that had been lost
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.56,0:00:43.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,对不起 今晚我要晚点儿回了\NSorry,but I'm gonna be late tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.23,0:00:46.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是因为Bogdan那家伙 他烦透了\NBogdan. He's got a bug up his butt
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.14,0:00:49.04,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们实际已经拍完最后一集了 \NWe've shot 2 episodes since 514
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.15,0:00:54.16,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是由于我们必须给Bryan和Jesse刮胡子换造型\NBut because we had to shave Bryan and alter Jesse
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.26,0:01:00.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以在运作上 这个第五季十四集的引子必须放在最后拍\NWe logistically just had to place this teaser at the very end of our filming
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.26,0:01:02.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以对啊 这就是我们的最后一天了\NSo..yeah,this is the last day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.27,0:01:06.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不仅仅是第五季第十四集的最后一天 更是全剧最后一天\NNot only of 514,but this is the last day of series filming
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.56,0:01:08.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,谢谢你亲爱的 我爱你 -我也爱你\NThank you honey,I love you,love you too
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.10,0:01:10.85,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡\NCutting
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:14.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这是我们告别的日子《绝命毒师》最后的摄制日\NIt's our farewell day,our last day of shooting Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.66,0:01:20.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,天气不错 华氏73或74度的样子 真是棒极了\NIt's beautiful,it's like 73 or 74 degrees,just fantastic
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.32,0:01:28.58,2,NTP,0,0,0,,数百人为这个剧投入了无尽的热爱和辛劳 以及他们的艺术天才\NSo many hundreds of people had put so much work and their love and effort and artistry
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.65,0:01:33.00,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有时候 我觉得我就像是来凑热闹的 \NThat I just feel someday it's like I'm along for the ride
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.08,0:01:34.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我现在也会这么想\NI feel like that way today a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.07,0:01:40.48,2,NTP,0,0,0,,今天非常糟糕 糟透了\NThis day is just terrible,awful,it's horrible
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.56,0:01:43.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在这一切开始之前 我完全没有想到\NI've no idea,back to the beginning of all this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.88,0:01:46.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个剧会走这么远\NThat the show would go as far as it's gone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.22,0:01:51.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,谁能想到这部剧会坚定地走到今天 并拥有这么多粉丝\NWho knew this would have such legs would go so far and have so many fans
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.87,0:01:59.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,绝不折中:《绝命毒师》最终季制作记录
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:02.73,2,NTP,0,0,0,,2004年2月 Vince和我正在打电话\NIt was in Feb,2004,Vince and I were talking on the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.84,0:02:06.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,偶然间 我提了一下我在纽约时报看到的一篇报道 \NFor some reason,I brought up this article that I read in new york times
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.90,0:02:10.21,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是关于一个在自己公寓里制冰毒的人的\NAbout a guy who was cooking meth in an apartment building
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.34,0:02:14.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不知怎的 这个话题让我们开始谈论 这个主意是多么棒\NAnd then somehow that morphed into us talking about that's probably a pretty good idea
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.41,0:02:19.03,2,NTP,0,0,0,,也许我们可以试试写个房车制毒 赚点外快的故事 \NMaybe we should go around in an RV cooking meth to make some extra money
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.13,0:02:22.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我还没反应过来 一份《绝命毒师》剧本就出炉了\NAnd then before I know it,suddenly there was a Breaking Bad script
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.20,0:02:25.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 我刚接手这部剧的创意时 关于要不要做下去\NActually the idea of doing the show when it came across my desk
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.34,0:02:28.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我的想法是 听起来有点意思 但风险也是有的\NWas,sounds interesting,a little bit risky
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.34,0:02:30.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是你知道 这就是我们 有冲劲儿\NBut you know,this is who we are,scrappy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.96,0:02:33.97,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们追求的就是 有趣的独特的大想法\NAnd we are gonna go for the big interesting,different idea
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.10,0:02:36.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而这就是一个 有趣的独特的大想法\NThis is certainly big interesting and different
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:42.95,2,NTP,0,0,0,,《绝命毒师》不再只是纸上谈兵的时机成熟了\NThe time had come where Breaking Bad was no longer going to be just a script and words on a page
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.04,0:02:44.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们想将它付诸现实\NWe wanted to make it a reality
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.77,0:02:48.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们找了网络合作伙伴AMC来帮助我们\NWe have found our network partner AMC to make that a reality
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.74,0:02:52.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们走了下流程 见了AMC的负责人 \NWe've had a process here,where we were going to meet with the chairman of the studio
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:56.08,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Michael Lynten希望他能支持我们\NMichael Lynten,to have him give us his blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.18,0:02:57.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们向我描述了剧情\NThey described the show to me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.43,0:03:01.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后我就说我来理一下 这是个高中化学老师的故事\NAnd I said so let me get this straight,this is about a high school chemistry teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:08.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,中年有家室 得了癌症 然后他决定走上邪路 成为了一个毒枭\NMiddle-aged,children,he has cancer and he decides to go off and become a crystal meth dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.85,0:03:09.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后他们说 对就是这样\NAnd they say that's right
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.05,0:03:11.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当时的会面如果是一部电影的话 会有紧张的咬指甲的瞬间\NIf it were movie there would have been be nail-scratch
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.75,0:03:15.33,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当时一片寂静 Michael从剧本中抬起头\NIt was just silence,Michael looks up from the paper
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.41,0:03:17.63,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他在听 却没和任何一个人作眼神交流\NHe is hearing everything but making no eye contact
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.71,0:03:23.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后他说道 这是我听过的 最疯狂最糟糕的电视剧创意\NAnd says,that is the craziest and worst idea for a television show I've ever heard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:26.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我不管谁写的剧本 这简直疯了\NAnd I don't really care who writes it,that's nuts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.66,0:03:29.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你必须明白 此时此刻我们已经投入了很多\NYou have to understand at this point we are so far in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.05,0:03:32.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而这个我们刚刚给Michael讲的故事\NAnd the story that we've just told Michael
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.95,0:03:34.91,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是我们抱着极大的信念来创作的\NHad done with so much conviction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.00,0:03:37.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们真的没有回头路可走\NThere's really no getting out if it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:41.09,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后他们说 我们坚信这个剧本的潜力 我们相信Vince\NAnd they said we really believe in this,we really believe in Vince
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.18,0:03:43.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们相信这个剧本会成为一流的电视剧\NAnd we feel that this can be a very terrific show
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.88,0:03:46.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后我说 嘿伙计们 这是你们自己的事业\NAnd I said hey guys,this is your career,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:49.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你们真的觉得这个有那么棒的话 那就做下去吧\NIf you really think that this is that great,you should go ahead with it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.88,0:03:53.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我不能说 还会有哪个台的头头会那样说\NI can't say that any other studio head would've said that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.39,0:03:57.44,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我真的要在这儿赞一下AMC\NAnd it's a great compliment in this place
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.54,0:04:00.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我真不确定 这剧放到其他哪个台能成\NI'm not sure the show was anywhere else would have actually made it into the air
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.96,0:04:03.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在我们为《绝命毒师》选角之前\NBefore we started on Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.28,0:04:06.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们刚刚为拉霍亚剧场完成选角任务\NWe had just finished casting for the La Jolla Playhouse
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.06,0:04:11.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan Cranston来为主角试读台词 我们都被他的表现震惊了\NAnd Bryan Cranston came in to read for the lead role and blew us away
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:18.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,对于Walter White这角色 他有着360度的完美素质\NBryan Cranston has the full 360 that you need for somebody like Walter White
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.66,0:04:19.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们是绝配\NIt was the perfect match
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.82,0:04:23.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以当我们去找Vince谈一些想法时\NSo when we went to talk to Vince about some ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:25.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们对Bryan Cranston是赞不绝口\NWe couldn't stop talking about Bryan Cranston
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.89,0:04:30.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而他恰巧是Vince开始选角时 脑中设想的那个演员\NWho was the actor that Vince had had in mind when he was starting to cast
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:32.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以那是一次心有灵犀般的交流\NSo it was a meeting of the minds
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:36.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Vince的支持是很重要的 因为你去一个电视台说\NAnd it was really helpful because when you go to a network
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.28,0:04:41.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你有一个新的剧情类电视剧的创意\NAnd you say for your brand new series drama
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.16,0:04:44.10,2,NTP,0,0,0,,却想要《马尔科姆的一家》中的爸爸来主演\NWe wanted to cast the dad from Malcom In The Middle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.18,0:04:46.91,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以想象你会得到啥反应\NYou can imagine the reaction you would get
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:50.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得 这剧本就是个精彩绝伦的文学作品\NI thought,this is an incredible piece of literature
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.90,0:04:54.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我非常想参演 让我的气味遍布这个角色\NI wanted to go in there and spray my scent all over that character
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.85,0:04:58.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我想要做个标记将它据为己有\NI wanted to mark it as mine
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:01.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,以至于让Vince回头再看这个角色时\NSo that when Vince Gilligan even look back at the character
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.02,0:05:05.33,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他都能闻到我的麝香 \NHe could smell my...my musk
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.40,0:05:08.95,2,NTP,0,0,0,,还要说 不知怎的 Bryan你好像从纸上冒出来了\Nand go I don't know why,Bryan,you coming off the page
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.04,0:05:11.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但那确实发生了\NBut that's what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.73,0:05:16.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,首播集的拍摄 导演Vince Gilligan
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.48,0:05:19.84,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们刚到片场时 大家好像很快就契合在一起了\NWhen we walked on set,everyone just sort off jelled
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.94,0:05:24.10,2,NTP,0,0,0,,以一种非常完美 非常独特的方式\NIn such a perfect unique way
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:29.41,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan和我之间 自第一天起就有一种化学反应\NAnd Bryan and I had this chemistry from day one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.53,0:05:32.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,让我们默契十足\NThat just really worked
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:39.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,很快你能意识到 这个项目里的人们真的是超一流的\NVery quickly,you begin to realize that the people connected to the project were really first rate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.43,0:05:44.84,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们有两次奥斯卡奖得主John Toll 他是我们的摄像指导\NWe had john toll who had won two Oscars,he was the cinematographer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:49.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以有很多人打来电话要求为我们免费工作\NSo there were people calling us up offering to work for free
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.31,0:05:53.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,只为了能在John Toll的团队里\NJust to be on a john toll crew
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.26,0:05:54.84,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我记得在To'Hajiilee时\NI remember out in To'Hajiilee
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.95,0:05:57.51,2,NTP,0,0,0,,一个非常寒冷的早上 我快冻死了\NIt was a quite chilling morning,I wimped out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:00.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我将Bryan拉到一边对他说\NAnd I said to Bryan,I took him aside and said
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.02,0:06:02.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你穿着内裤感觉怎么样\NHow do you feel about the underpants
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.93,0:06:06.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他说 你知道吗 你觉得我能穿的最尴尬的东西是什么 \NHe said,you know what  what's the most embarrassing thing I could be dressed in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.54,0:06:08.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我说紧身内裤\NI said tighty-whity underpants
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:11.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他说那就是我要穿的 因为那样对角色来说是对的\NHe said that's what I'm gonna wear,because that's what's right for the character
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.61,0:06:18.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我想把自己塑造成 一个臃肿的不修边幅的人 一个对生活失望的人\NI intended to be over-weight,I wanted to be a guy,who went to seed,who didn't care any more
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.59,0:06:22.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第一集里有场戏 我要从房车里跳下来\NSo popping out of that RV in the pilot episode
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.31,0:06:26.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,观众们可以看到我内裤上面一堆赘肉\NAnd having my love handles fold over my tighty-whity underwear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:31.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那可不是我真的想呈现给世界的样子\NIt wasn't the image that I really would like to present to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:33.95,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是不管怎样 你需要鼓起勇气这样去做\NAnd yet,you had to have the courage to do so
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.07,0:06:40.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在沙漠腹地里拍摄的时候\NIn the middle of the desert shooting of the show
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.15,0:06:41.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他就只穿个内裤 在那里跳来舞去\NHe was dancing around in his underwear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.56,0:06:46.97,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后我心里想 噢上帝啊 我爱这个男人\NAnd I just thought to myself,my god,I love this man
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.05,0:06:51.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,谁知道我们的男一号会这么有意思\NThe idea of that number 1 on the call-sheet would be able to have so much fun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.08,0:06:53.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而且我们也可以不怎么把他当回事\NAnd not taking him so seriously all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:58.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,特别是当我们拍一个异常紧张的场景时 这是一件美妙的事\NParticularly when we are doing such intense scenes,was a wonderful thing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.84,0:07:00.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡\NCut
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:09.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,非常幸运的是 当我们第一次放映第一集的时候\NLuckily the first time we had a screening of the pilot episode
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.75,0:07:13.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我就知道Sony和AMC喜欢它了\NI knew already that SONY liked it and AMC liked it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:16.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我记得Josh Sapen说过 如果将试播集延长20分钟\NI remember Josh Sapen say,did you know if you added 20 minutes to that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.06,0:07:19.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那一集可能会成为年度最佳独立电影\NThat pilot is probably the best independent film of the year
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.06,0:07:25.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在SONY试播了这一集 是给演职人员们看的\NBut we had a screening at SONY,and it was for the cast and crew
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.44,0:07:32.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,很谦虚地说 这一集的完美让所有人都充满了敬畏之情\NIn the most modest way possible,we are just in such awe of how beautiful it looked
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.03,0:07:34.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,导演的手法简直绝了\NJust the way it was directed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.55,0:07:39.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们爆发了雷鸣般的掌声和欢呼 我们是那么自豪 完全被征服了\NWe all just started roaring and applauding,we were so proud,we are so blown away
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:43.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我当时完全不能相信 自己会是这部剧的一部分\NAnd I thought I can't believing I'm part of this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.36,0:07:47.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那会儿我仍不理解 这个故事怎么能被拍成电视剧呢\NI still didn't understand how this thing would be turned into a television series
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.47,0:07:50.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我仍然不明白Vince的脑子里在想些什么\NAnd I still didn't understand what was in Vince's head
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.34,0:07:55.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我没法说 我只看了一集试播集 就说了啊 太棒了 \NSo,no I honestly cannot tell you that I looked at the pilot and said oh,my god,eureka
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.69,0:07:56.85,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但你明白 这是事实\NYou know that's the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.93,0:08:00.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那些看了试播集的人们的疑惑之一是\NOne of the things that concern people when they saw the finished pilot
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.78,0:08:03.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们会说这太棒了 不过它到底在讲什么呢\NThey said this is great,but what's the show
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.88,0:08:06.61,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我不确定Vince或我们其他任何编剧\NI'm not sure that Vince,or any of us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:08.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,真正知道这个电视剧究竟是讲什么的\Nreally know what the show was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.56,0:08:09.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们只知道自己刚开了个头\NWe knew what we've set up
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.86,0:08:12.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,想着 天啊 如今咱们可一定要完成它了\NI was like oh my god,now we've gotta finish it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.26,0:08:19.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,拍摄《绝命毒师》是一场非常狂野的旅行\NThe journey of Breaking Bad was a wild ride
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.96,0:08:22.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们并不知道走进了什么世界\NWe didn't know what we are going to get into
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.37,0:08:26.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第一季播出了 我们向世界呈现了7集\NSeason 1 we go on the air,we got 7 episodes to show the world
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.79,0:08:29.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,从最初的9集减少了两集 这是因为当年的编剧罢工\NDown from 9 because of the writer strike
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.58,0:08:32.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你好奇第一季为啥只有7集\NIf you are wondering why there are only 7 episodes of the season 1 of Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.05,0:08:35.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那是因为那年发生了编剧罢工\NThat's because there was a writer strike that year
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:39.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但Vince还是想出了一个在7集里完结的办法\NVince figured out a way to make it a complete season in 7 episodes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.27,0:08:43.63,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们最初只有很少的观众 我的感觉就是 啥 有没有搞错\NWe had very few viewers,to me it was like,what?come on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.79,0:08:45.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,怎么没有更多的人看呢\NWhy aren't more people watching the show
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:53.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,发现这剧连当年的谷歌搜索排行榜都没上 我当时就震惊了\NAnd I was a little bit dumbfounded that it didn't seem to be registering at all in the Zeitgeist
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.87,0:08:59.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,收视率一般般 但也有一小拨坚定的追随者\NVery moderate ratings very small,but mighty following
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:02.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Dean当时正在和我讨论收视率的事 他问我看了没\NDean was talking about our ratings and he asked me if I looked at that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:05.74,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我说没有 因为我想 你能怎么办呢\NAnd I said,no,because,I was like,what are you gonna do
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.85,0:09:09.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,表演的更好些  你知道 我在尝试了\NAct harder  well you know,I'm kind of trying
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.09,0:09:12.00,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但如果真的需要收视率的话 我会真的非常努力的\NBut if we need more numbers,I'm really gonna focus
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.09,0:09:14.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,万分感谢影视评论家和专栏记者们\NThank goddess for the TV critics and the journalists
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.87,0:09:18.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为他们喜欢我们这剧 我们必须感谢他们\NBecause they liked us and I had to give them a lot of credit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.33,0:09:21.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为他们在早期的大力支持 我们才能继续播下去\NThey really did keep us on the air in those early days
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.12,0:09:26.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我听说我们没有差评 我们没有一个差评\NI was told there are no bad reviews,we didn't have a bad review
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.36,0:09:31.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第一季以Bryan赢得艾美奖剧情类最佳男主角为高潮\NAnd that first season culminated with Bryan Cranston winning the Emmy for best actor in a drama
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.88,0:09:35.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后突然之间 人们突然开始说\NAnd then all of a sudden it seems like people start going
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.61,0:09:37.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,慢着 这个《绝命毒师》是个什么剧 \NOh wait a second what's this Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.11,0:09:42.44,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第二季 我们的首要目标就是拍一季完整的\NIn season 2,we got our first goal at a whole season
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:49.41,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第二季的时候我们会因为Walt和Jesse的对手戏而异常激动\NBy season 2 we all got really excited about having Walt and Jesse scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.49,0:09:53.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就好像慢慢成了两个主角的剧\NIt kinda felt like it was turning into a two-hander
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:56.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,换句话说 这剧很大程度上是关于Walter的\NIn another words,the show is very much about Walter White
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.60,0:09:59.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是渐渐地也变成了Jesse的剧\NBut it's also becoming very much about Jesse Pinkman
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.44,0:10:01.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Michael Slovis在第二季的时候加入了我们\NMichael Slovis started with us in season 2
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:05.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在视觉方面他把本片推上了更高的一层楼\NAnd I think very much elevated the show in terms of its look
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.33,0:10:07.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,氛围更加黑暗 人物故事更加如履薄冰\NHe made it even darker,even edgier
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.59,0:10:14.21,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第二季带来了Bob和Jonathan\NIt brought the arrival of Bob Odenkirk and Jonathan Banks
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.28,0:10:16.62,2,NTP,0,0,0,,整个剧在不断演进 故事变得越来越庞大\NThe show was evolving and it was getting bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.82,0:10:24.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第三季则更加黑暗了\NSeason 3 gets a little bit darker
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.06,0:10:30.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,一开始观众看到的 就是两个穿着体面的冷血杀手兄弟\NViewers introduced to the well dressed cousins who turn out to be very dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.83,0:10:37.04,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在第三季的时候 我才感觉我们的剧真真正正的开始腾飞了\NBy the time we get to season 3 I began to feel our little show had really taken flight
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.14,0:10:42.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第三季结束后 时代周刊发布了\NAt the end of season 3,TIME magazine published
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.17,0:10:45.51,2,NTP,0,0,0,,过去一年里电视剧中的优秀单集前十名\NThe top 10 episodes of television in the previous year
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.61,0:10:49.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Michelle Maclaren执导的《一分钟》那一集就是第一名\NAnd the Michelle Maclaren's One Minute was the number 1 show
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.54,0:10:57.62,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当Gus加入进来时 我们达到了一个之前完全没想到的高度\NWhen Gus Fring came in,we are now doing this on a level that was not possible to foresee
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:11:04.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Giancarlo诠释了一个电视史上最足智多谋的反派形象\NGiancarlo Esposito brought the most intense villain in history of television
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.87,0:11:07.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,大规模制毒和超级实验室的想法出现了\NMass producing and the idea of a super lab
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.05,0:11:13.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那个超级制毒实验室绝对是一个转折点 视觉上的 情节上的\NThe lab was definitely a turning point,visually,physically
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.63,0:11:18.03,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第三季还特别是小粉失去清白的转折点\NSeason 3 was really the loss of innocence for Jesse in particular
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.12,0:11:22.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在第三季结束时他开枪杀了那个化学家 \NThe very last moment of season 3 was him pulling the trigger
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.17,0:11:24.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,从而验证了自己的确是个坏人\NAnd proving he was the bad guy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.94,0:11:34.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,艾美提名捷报不断 Bryan和Aaron都因第三季的表现拿奖了\NThe Emmy noms continued and Bryan won for season 3 Aaron won for season 3
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.72,0:11:39.40,2,NTP,0,0,0,,非常激动人心 这是他们完美合作的最好明证\NWhich was very exciting and I think a real validation of that partnership
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:43.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,三连折桂艾美 真正让人们开始谈论起了《绝命毒师》\NThese 3 Emmys in a row really had people talking about Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.50,0:11:46.07,2,NTP,0,0,0,,特别是之前还没听说过的那些人\NPeople who otherwise might not have known about the show
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.16,0:11:49.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,直到第三季开播以后\NIt wasn't until about after season 3 had aired
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.86,0:11:53.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,才有不少的观众都在看了\NThat was like oh,there was quite a few people that watched the show
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.24,0:11:56.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这部剧的成功开始显露了\NThe success of the show was becoming apparent
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:12:00.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Vince和《绝命毒师》第三季都获得了作家指南奖\NVince won and the show won for season 3 for the writers guild awards
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:04.26,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Stephen King将它称作史上最好的剧之一\NStephen king called it,one of the greatest show of all time
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:07.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan和Aaron上了《滚石》的封面\NBryan and Aaron appeared on the cover of rolling stone
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.76,0:12:09.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,神呐 这得是多高的曝光度啊\NAnd man,what a highlight that was
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.02,0:12:14.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后 第四季变得越来越危险了\NAnd then,by season 4,it got incredibly dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:23.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,现在 全都是关于老白的自负 面子 贪婪和权力欲\NNow,it's all about his ego,and being respected,and greed and power
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.47,0:12:27.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,每一季都有更多的观众 更多的奖项\NEach season,more people are watching the show,more awards
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:31.03,2,NTP,0,0,0,,更多的关注 而且评论界也是持续看好\NMore attention,the reviews continued to be wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.13,0:12:36.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我想那就是为什么Vince好像在说 嘿 我们可不想一直霸占头条\NAnd I think that's part of why Vince was like hey we do not want to overstay our welcome
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.86,0:12:38.10,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我赢了\NI won
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.41,0:12:41.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,现在我们走到了第五季 \NSo now we get to season 5
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.80,0:12:44.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不幸的是 在我的编剧团队的帮助下我意识到\NUnfortunately,I came to realization with the help of my writers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.06,0:12:49.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们只有16集左右的故事可以拍了\NThat we had about only 16 or more episodes of story left to us
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.39,0:12:53.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Vince一开始就说了他准备在这剧表现良好的时候结束\NVince said from the beginning that he wanted to end the show when it's doing well
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.74,0:12:56.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而他现在只有这么多集剩下了\NAnd that he only had only so many episodes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.78,0:13:00.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这并不是一个容易的决定 但是在某种程度上 我知道必须要完结了\NIt's not an easy decision to make,but at a certain point,I knew it had to end
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.81,0:13:05.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,冒一点风险 结束的早总比结束太晚更好\NI know it's better to risk ending it a bit too soon than to end too late
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.77,0:13:20.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,《绝命毒师》编剧办公室 2012年12月
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.74,0:13:31.53,2,NTP,0,0,0,,作为整部剧的制作人 我最重要的工作是首席编剧\NMy most important job as a show runner of Breaking Bad is head writer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.60,0:13:33.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我要做的最重要的事\NThat the most important thing I do
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.65,0:13:36.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就是带领着编剧工作室 并确保把故事讲好\NIs run the writer's room and ensured the story gets told
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.23,0:13:41.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我只是觉得之前我们讨论时\NI just feel like there's..when we were talking about it last week
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.64,0:13:44.52,2,NTP,0,0,0,,剧情深化之前还有很多家庭关系要理清楚\NI feel like there's was a lot about family before it actually takes off
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.61,0:13:49.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,比如 说真的 因为马上就要拍这几集了\NLike what  I'm serious because I'm too close to it right now
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.05,0:13:53.85,2,NTP,0,0,0,,写最后一段剧情是一个挑战 部分是因为大家真的很爱我们剧\NBreaking the final leg was a challenge,partially because people do love the show
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.95,0:13:56.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们真的想好好回馈大家\NAnd we really wanted to pay it off
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.45,0:14:00.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Skyler必须为了她的孩子保持坚强  \NShe has to remain strong for her kids
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.95,0:14:03.73,2,NTP,0,0,0,,要不就是她彻底崩溃无法再坚强起来\NOr else she just so devastated that she can't remain strong any more
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.83,0:14:07.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,也是因为我们剧在评论界美誉连连 我们更加压力山大\NThere was a lot of pressure because also the show has been critically acclaimed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.86,0:14:11.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那逼着我们想创意到想到发晕\NAnd that can create a sense of creative vertigo
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.35,0:14:16.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Walt Jr 这条故事线也得发生点什么\NSomething you need to transpire with Junior
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.12,0:14:19.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这样才可能会导致接下来的事情的发生\Nthat forces...perhaps forces this issue
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.95,0:14:24.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有如此多的拼图我们要将它们环环相扣\NThere were so many of these puzzle pieces that we sort of wanted to lock together
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.22,0:14:27.07,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有两种可能 要么他们和他一起走\NThere are two possibilities,they can leave town and come with him or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:29.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,要么他们分道扬镳\NThey can leave town,and go somewhere completely different
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.84,0:14:33.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们想要成为那种为数不多的剧 不狗尾续貂\NWe wanted to be one of the few shows that ended like we begin
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.76,0:14:37.04,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你知道 就是超牛逼的那种\NWhich was you know,kicking ass
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.09,0:14:52.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,最终季摄制首日 Q片场 阿尔伯克基
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.12,0:15:05.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,开始我们最后一程的工作时 我的心情很是复杂\NI feel a mixture of things being here at the beginning of this last push
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.93,0:15:09.52,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我现在倒不会感到很怀旧 你可能会那样想\NI don't feel as nostalgic right now as you might expect
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.60,0:15:13.91,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我主要是感到的是紧张 我是个多愁善感的人\NI feel mainly nervous,I'm very sentimental person,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.99,0:15:16.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当一切结束时 我会超级想念这个剧\NI'm gonna miss this mightily when it's over
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.65,0:15:25.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我想这部剧的每个工作人员都理解 这部剧需要高调谢幕\NI think everybody working on Breaking Bad understands the need to end the show on a high note
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.67,0:15:28.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我当然不希望它结束 我希望它一直继续下去\NI don't want it to end,I want it to go on forever
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:33.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,可能最重要的原因 在我看是\NProbably the most important reason for that,for me,is that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:35.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们已经成了一个大家庭\NWe've created a family here
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.81,0:15:38.51,2,NTP,0,0,0,,兄弟 一切可好\N-brother,how is everything going
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.60,0:15:40.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你啥时候来的\N-when did you get in the town
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:42.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,昨天三点半 -真棒\N-yesterday at 3.30 -nice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.50,0:15:45.03,2,NTP,0,0,0,,快结束了 太难受了\NOh the end is near,so sad
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.14,0:15:51.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在很棒的Q片场 准备预读第五季第九集的剧本\NWe are at the fantastic Q studios and we are about to do the table read of S5E09
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.60,0:15:54.84,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这是第五季第二部分的第一集\NOur first episode back in season 5B
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.96,0:15:56.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,瞧啊\N-look at this
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.96,0:15:59.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你怎么样 见到你真好\N-how are you,good to see you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.12,0:16:07.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,每一季开拍的时候 我感觉就好像回到了大本营\NI felt every season like you get to go back to camp
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:11.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你等不及要和朋友们团聚\NAnd you can't wait to go and you can't wait see your friends
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.26,0:16:12.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所有人都将团聚在一起\NAnd everybody is gonna come back
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.52,0:16:14.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Anna Gunn  哟\NAnna Gunn  everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.85,0:16:19.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你怎么样亲爱的 -我很好 你真美\NHow are you,honey -I'm good,you look beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.68,0:16:24.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们相处得很好 而Bryan好像是领袖\NThe way we all approached it,it were sort of led by Bryan
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.21,0:16:33.44,2,NTP,0,0,0,,让我们好好珍惜品味我们在一起的每一份每一秒\NLet's savor and relish every second that we have together and let's enjoy every last minute of it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.54,0:16:36.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为我们是这么幸运能拥有这一切\NBecause we are so lucky to have this
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.11,0:16:39.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你 -你开车来的吗 \NNice to see you -did you drive or
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.26,0:16:41.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不 我昨天乘飞机来的\NNo,I flew,yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.25,0:16:44.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在我们开始之前 请Gilligan先发言\NBefore we start anything,I hand it over to Mr.Gilligan
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.45,0:16:57.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,欢迎大家回来 这是我们最后一次开拍前预读会议\NEverybody welcome,to our final pre-production table read
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.41,0:17:02.74,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这集超赞 是由Peter Gould执笔的 他在哪 -他读Badger的部分\NFor this wonderful episode that,where's Peter,that Peter Gould wrote -he's reading Badger
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.85,0:17:06.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这一集由Bryan Cranston执导\NAnd this episode directed by Mr. Bryan Cranston
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:16.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,《绝命毒师》第五季第九集 染血的钱\NEpisode of Breaking Bad titled blood money episode 509
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.27,0:17:21.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么是Keylee\NWhy Kaylee Ehrmantraut
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:25.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她需要一个人照顾她\NShe needs someone to look after her
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:31.74,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Mike完全有能力照顾他的小孙女\NMike is more than capable of taking care of his own granddaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.82,0:17:34.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,参与读稿试演感觉很棒\NIt's amazing to sit in a read-through
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.48,0:17:37.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,大家分开了差不多四五个月\NWith those who have been away for a hiatus for 4 or 5 month
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:40.41,2,NTP,0,0,0,,看着这些超棒的演员坐下来\NAnd to watch these brilliant actors sit down and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.50,0:17:42.78,2,NTP,0,0,0,,高超地表演这些台词\NDo these worlds,embrace these worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.86,0:17:45.97,2,NTP,0,0,0,,好似他们过去五个月都在故事里生活着\NAs if they were living in them everyday for the last 5 months
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.04,0:17:50.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如果Mike还活着 你接下来都要担惊受怕\NIf Mike were out there you'll have to look over your shoulder for the rest of your life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.91,0:17:53.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那不是你做事的风格\NThat's not how you do things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.17,0:17:58.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为他已经死了 而且你知道这一点\NI think he is dead and I think you know that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.17,0:18:06.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,先上收敛水 对吧\NAstringent goes on first
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.08,0:18:12.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我脸上那丁点的水分也要没了\NSo any moisture that I happened to have in my face is gone
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.53,0:18:17.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我就知道Bryan是最适合演Walter的人\NI knew Bryan is the right guy,to play Walter White,I knew he was the man for the role
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.03,0:18:26.09,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以现在我们要做的 就是使他看上去更老一些 更沧桑一些\NSo what we are doing here is trying to age him,and decay him,somewhat
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.20,0:18:29.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,可怜的Walt\NPoor Walt
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:32.97,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他唤醒这个角色的方式 诠释这个角色的方式\NThe way he arose the occasion,to play this part,this character
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.04,0:18:37.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,都是令人惊艳的 他很在乎这个角色的一切\NIs stunning,he cares deeply about this character and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:40.53,2,NTP,0,0,0,,对于每个细节都精益求精\NGetting details of this character right
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.30,0:18:46.10,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他注定要演这个角色 在我心中 这就是命运\NHe was meant to play this part,it was fate,it was destiny,in my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.19,0:18:49.82,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan是一个彻底不同于Walt的人\NBryan is a completely different person than Walt
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.92,0:18:54.89,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当他换上Walt的皮肤 上了妆之后\NAnd when he put on that skin,when he puts on the make up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.95,0:18:59.89,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他就变成了Walt 而且是一场真正的变形\NHe transforms into Walt white,and it's a true transformation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.99,0:19:07.07,2,NTP,0,0,0,,从一个热爱生活的 本质上非常乐观和幸福的一个人\NFrom a man who loves life,and who is naturally very happy and optimistic
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.17,0:19:12.47,2,NTP,0,0,0,,转变成了内心黑暗 很具破坏性的Walt\NTo Walt,who has so much darkness and so much damage
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.56,0:19:14.95,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们是如此的不同\NThe two could not be more distinct
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.15,0:19:20.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我从一开始就看到了Walt生命的动态走向\NI realized that the dynamic aspect of Walt white from the very beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.30,0:19:23.78,2,NTP,0,0,0,,现在是时候说再见了\NAnd now it's the time to say goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.89,0:19:27.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他是一个被打倒的人 \NHe was a beaten-down man
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.54,0:19:34.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然已经身形憔悴 他仍然能专注于手边的任务\NAnd even in his physical depletion he was able to focus on the task at hand
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.33,0:19:41.41,2,NTP,0,0,0,,托起颧骨会使得脸颊看起来下陷了\NBy building up the cheekbones,it appears as if you are hollowing out cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.49,0:19:44.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,高颧骨会让我看上去更瘦 \NBuild this up I'll look thinner,like I've lost weight
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.55,0:19:46.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个火鸡一样的脖子\NAnd this of course the turkey neck
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.33,0:19:50.04,2,NTP,0,0,0,,会让他看起来短时间内掉了很多斤\NMakes it like he's lost a lot of weight,in a short period of time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.14,0:19:52.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,由于电视剧每集分开制作的模式\NBecause of the way episodic television was produced
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.07,0:19:55.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,每一集我们都会有不同的导演\NWe've had different directors for each episode
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.39,0:19:59.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有时是嘉宾导演 有时是我 有时是Vince\NSometimes it's a guest director,sometimes it's me,sometimes it's Vince Gillian
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.96,0:20:03.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有时是我们编剧之一 有时是我们的摄像指导Mike Slovis\NSometimes it's one of our writers,sometimes it's our cinematographer Mike Slovis
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.02,0:20:06.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有时是Bryan Cranston\NAnd sometime it's Bryan Cranston
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.15,0:20:10.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在准备过程中 我最喜欢的一个发现就是\NOne of my favorite things that I discovered in the prep
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.32,0:20:12.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Walt家被毁的很惨\NWas the destruction of the White house
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.91,0:20:15.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而我第一眼看到那被摧毁的样子后感到很沮丧\Nand that how depressing that was to see it first time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.34,0:20:19.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,看到Walt家的那种情况就好像是 你踏过的是一片坟墓\NIt's almost like trampling on a grave when you look at the white house in that condition
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.77,0:20:25.58,2,NTP,0,0,0,,《绝命毒师》有两位老爸\NWe have two dads on Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.68,0:20:28.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,一位是Bryan 另一个是Mike Slovis\NOne of them was Bryan Cranston one of them is Mike Slovis
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.18,0:20:31.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他是我们的摄像指导\NMike Slovis is our cinematographer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.46,0:20:35.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他负责所有的摄影和画面工作\NAs such he is responsible for all things photographic on the series
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.29,0:20:40.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我提出来是因为 这样拍摄的话 你的背景是一堵白墙\NThe only reason I say,is because,this is you against a flat wall
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.59,0:20:42.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,关于摄像指导 人们常说\NIt's often been said about cinematographers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.30,0:20:45.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你要么拍的好 要么拍的快 但你不可能两者兼得\NYou either get good,or you get fast,but you never get both
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.01,0:20:51.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而Michael却是那种少见的能兼顾二者的大师\NMichael Slovis is the rare cinematographer who is both great and he's fast
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.71,0:20:54.34,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你们两个都看我演示\NWatch me from both,because
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.02,0:20:57.27,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你走到这里\NSo you come in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.39,0:21:01.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这里切成主人公视角 -对 切成主人公视角\NWe got the POV,-I got the POV
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.14,0:21:03.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这之后再切回你继续前进 这样可以拍到有更有趣的背景\NNow you go and you have a really interesting background
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.01,0:21:07.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-还有人物的反应 -比对着一面白墙拍要好\N-and I get your reaction -as opposed to this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.55,0:21:08.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,从一开始 \NAt the very beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.78,0:21:13.91,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我和Vince对于这部戏的配色走向 就有一个大致的计划\NVince and I had a plan of where the entire series should go in terms of pallet and color
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.99,0:21:18.47,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当Walt越来越堕落成一个罪恶的人\NAs Walt descended more into this really evil being
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.58,0:21:21.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我让这个剧的色调变得越来越黑暗\NI saw the show getting darker and darker and darker
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.62,0:21:25.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有这么好的剧本 我能用更大的画笔作出更宏大的作品\NWith materials this great,I can paint with a bigger brush,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.22,0:21:27.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为故事强大到足以支持那样的场面\NBecause it can support it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.77,0:21:29.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是我们正在做的工作 \NSo this is what we are doing now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.69,0:21:35.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,用Heisenberg本人的视角来拍摄 他走入废墟旧宅的过程\NIs the POV of Heisenberg walking down his old burnt-down life
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.79,0:21:45.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我是Andrew Voegeli A机位摄像\NMy name is Andrew Voegeli,and I am the A-camera operator on Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.46,0:21:49.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,拍摄了第二季至第五季下部分\NFrom season 2 through season 6
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.64,0:21:59.61,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这样的大制作 从头到尾每天的摄制工作都非常累人\NBreaking Bad being hell of a show,it's just a grueling process,you know,from start to finish everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.54,0:22:05.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,拍摄这部电视剧对体力要求很高\NSo physically it's a very demanding show,and very..very hard
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.19,0:22:18.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡\NAnd.. And we cut
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.58,0:22:25.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,拍第五季第九集的第一天 我们为下一集开了一次概念研讨会\NThe first day that we were shooting 509,we did a concept meeting for episode 510
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.86,0:22:28.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,大家好么 \NHow are u guys doing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.30,0:22:32.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们把剧情卡片贴墙上了 -好的 不错\NWe're putting our cards on board -alright good
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.45,0:22:34.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,等你们回来 再看看还剩几个点子没毙掉\NWe'll see how many survive when you get back
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.06,0:22:41.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在为第五季第十集做准备 这集是Tom Schnauze写的\NWe're prepping for E510,which was written by tom Schnauze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.59,0:22:44.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Tom可以说是我的老朋友了\NAnd tom is arguably my oldest friend
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.72,0:22:49.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,1986年 我们在纽约大学蒂诗艺术学院的电影系结识\NWe met in 1986 at Tisch school of the arts at NYU,the film school
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.44,0:22:54.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,剧本写的超赞 爱你们\NGreat job on the scripts,very great yeah..thank you  great writing,I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.52,0:23:01.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Diana 我们讨论了下 有没有可能拍摄一些背部视角的镜头\NDiana there has been some conversations about doing some via-backs potentially here,for the point of view
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:05.95,2,NTP,0,0,0,,90年代末拍《X档案》的时候我认识了Michelle\NI met Michelle back in the late 1990s on the X-files….
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.05,0:23:07.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他去我们看的地方了 \NHe went down the neighborhoods that we were looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.03,0:23:10.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,视觉上非常棒 而且还都有栅栏\NWhich was visually fantastic and all have fences
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.99,0:23:15.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,每次她来导演一集的时候 我都能放下心来\NEvery time she sets up to direct an episode of Breaking Bad,I can relax quite a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.69,0:23:19.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道她会关注到所有重要的问题\NBecause I know she is gonna ask all the questions that needed get asked
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.39,0:23:23.66,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我是觉得 你和Bryan的那集没必要用不一样的景\NIt seems to me that there's no reason for you to a different neighborhood your episode and Bryan's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.75,0:23:26.64,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 那片没有栅栏之类的东西\NSo..not having the fences and things…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.73,0:23:28.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Vince的优点在于 他是个很本色的人\NThe great thing about Vince,is that Vince doesn't change
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.77,0:23:31.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他爱这个片场 又有领导力\NHe loves his set,a great tone for everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.38,0:23:35.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他会说我们要有专业人员的样子 但也要有乐子\NYou know let's endorse how's professional,but let's have some fun
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.91,0:23:41.68,2,NTP,0,0,0,,任务重大 我们来好好干吧 这就是我们的工作方式\NWe've got a lot of work ahead of us,that's do great work..that's our approach
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.76,0:23:46.64,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Tom 你是想穿着工装背带裤里面还不穿衣服吗\NTom,do you man,do you wanna dress like you are in the barrel overall and no-shirt look
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.18,0:23:57.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,把书拿在这\NThis is down here
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.67,0:24:05.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第一幕 Dean从厕所里走出来的时候 \NWhen Dean Norris comes out of bathroom,the very first act
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.51,0:24:10.47,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他要承担着惊天发现的重压\NHe is carrying the weight of discovery on the shoulders
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.66,0:24:14.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,关于怎么演 我们有好几个想法\NThere was a variety of different ideas on how to play that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.55,0:24:15.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,观众们都在想 \NThe audiences are wondering
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.79,0:24:20.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如今Hank从厕所里出来该是什么想法 他会怎么做\NNow what is hank gonna feel when he comes out of that bathroom,what's he gonna do
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.79,0:24:27.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为 Hank的心理活动应该是 我该怎么说 就说我肚子不舒服 \NThe process to me is..what should I say ..just say I'm not feeling well
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.52,0:24:30.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后你的视线来找我 屋角的镜头打过来\NAnd you are looking after me,camera around the corner
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.66,0:24:34.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为你拿着那本书 所以赶紧把它藏在后面\NCuz' you got that book you are about ready to put that book behind your back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.41,0:24:40.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得剧情很棒 Hank追踪了那么久 终于要抓到这条白鲸了\NI think it's great that hank is gonna get to finally catch the white whale that he's been chasing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.09,0:24:45.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,单单凭这本书 所有的一切都连结起来 昭示着不幸的事实\NYou know all this lone book..and then after that all help brings them unfortunately
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.53,0:24:49.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,56秒 开拍\N56 secs,and action
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.50,0:25:10.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,还可以怎么拍 还有其他的想法吗 \NAnything you would do differently  either one of you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.16,0:25:13.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这时的Hank要想 Walt在哪呢\NRight now,he is thinking where is Walt..
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.17,0:25:18.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,可以是 他整个人好像僵了一样 大脑发懵\NOne way he's just almost like zombified.. Like he's in his hell head
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.93,0:25:24.40,2,NTP,0,0,0,,自己往哪走都不清楚了 这一切都说得通吗 \NJust not even know where he is going..does that make any sense
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.50,0:25:27.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,很多剧情分析都是在拍摄的每分每秒进行的\NLots of analysis goes into every single moment of Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.92,0:25:35.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan做导演的时候 他对编剧们的建议相当开放\NAnd when Bryan Cranston is directing,he is so open to notes from writers
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.21,0:25:36.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我一直很欣赏他这一点\NI always impressed by that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.67,0:25:40.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是Hank也要留神提防Walt进来 \NBut he has the awareness to look out for Walt coming in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.64,0:25:45.09,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为他走到起居室时 是可以听见你的\NI would say when he gets to the living room,he could hear you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.20,0:25:47.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,或者是厨房那边 -他不时地能听见你\NOr he'd be in the kitchen there -he could hear you at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.28,0:25:50.95,2,NTP,0,0,0,,只要稍微像这样 明白吗 -好的\NBut in...till end it's just like,alright,you know -OK
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.65,0:25:57.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Dean 这个镜头再试一次彻底懵掉的Hank\NSo Dean,try one where you dumbstruck by this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.43,0:26:01.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,下半身在走 上面胳膊摆在头上\NSometimes part of you is walking,part of you is up here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.10,0:26:12.33,2,NTP,0,0,0,,作为导演一定要认识到 整个剧组是协作性质的\NYou have to embrace the collaborative nature that it is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.43,0:26:15.38,2,NTP,0,0,0,,否则就麻烦了\NAnd if you don't you are gonna be in trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.48,0:26:19.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,要么大家认为你太独裁 不愿意跟你工作\NEither people would hate work with you because you are dictatorial
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.88,0:26:24.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,只能以我的方法行事 这种想法是行不通的\NLike my way is the only way kind of thing,and that's just not true
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.24,0:26:27.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我必须要参考各种各样的意见\NYou have to allow for a variety of different opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.55,0:26:37.33,2,NTP,0,0,0,,深呼吸....往前走\NTake deep breath..and go
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.86,0:26:44.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡\NAnd cut -cutting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.85,0:26:49.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得就是这样的一种合作精神造就了《绝命毒师》 \NI think that level of collaboration is what makes Breaking Bad work
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.00,0:26:52.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,让每一个场景都成为精品\NIt what makes this individual scene work
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.59,0:26:54.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Dean 你觉得这次怎么样 \NHow do you feel about that Dean
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.46,0:26:56.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-不错 -有区别吗 \NAlright good. -any different
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.80,0:26:59.16,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-老实说的确是不同了\NIt's a honestly a different thing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.29,0:27:03.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-喜欢吗 -我觉得非常好\NGot three of them,do you like that'  I think that was great
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.96,0:27:08.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-我非常喜欢\NI really like it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.71,0:27:12.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们思路相当快 能够把我脑子里的\NThey think so quickly,and able to take the idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.20,0:27:16.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,某些的有趣想法迅速地转换为现实\NThat something tickles me,turning into a concrete result so fast
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.87,0:27:19.40,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是快乐之处\NThat's really that's the fun of it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.27,0:27:22.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这是剧组的劳模 \NThis is the hardest working person on the crew here
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.47,0:27:28.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Helen Caldwell 本片场记\NHelen Caldwell,she was our script supervisor
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.30,0:27:31.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她自己就是一个部门\NShe is a department of one
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.71,0:27:36.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以每次开各部门会议 她都要到场\NSo when they have department meetings,she has to be there
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.48,0:27:41.52,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们是做记录的 包括拍摄的过程 资料打印事宜\NWe keep track of stuff..keep track of every shot..what get printed what doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.62,0:27:44.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,演员们站起来说了哪些话 \NWhat line will say when they stood up and move..
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.50,0:27:48.04,2,NTP,0,0,0,,又停在哪一句上了 往左转了还是往右转了 \NWhat word did they stop on,did they turn it right or left..
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.14,0:27:55.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,演员们要是漏词了 我就得上前去告诉他 你搞砸了\NAny actors drop a line,I would actually go in there and tell him: You screwed up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.33,0:28:00.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她真的是这样 她会走过来这样说 你是故意不说这句的 \NYeah she will come in and go Did you want to drop this line,was that a choice or
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.66,0:28:03.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-还是失误了 -然后我就哎呀……\NBoo-boo..you know,I'd go: Ah…
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.50,0:28:17.47,2,NTP,0,0,0,,自第一集后 第五季第九集最后的对峙场景就是我们最期待的\NThe final conversation in S5E09 is something we've been waiting for ever since the end of the pilot
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.57,0:28:19.82,2,NTP,0,0,0,,自从Walt决定成为罪犯 \NEver since Walt decided to become a criminal
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.90,0:28:24.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,把自己放在Hank的瞄准镜下之后\Nand therefore put himself in his brother-in-law's gun sights,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.21,0:28:26.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这就是我们等待的时刻\NThis is it,this is the moment
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.86,0:28:30.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,大致就是这样 抡上来....\NSo the idea is....come in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.25,0:28:37.16,2,NTP,0,0,0,,和兼任导演的演员合作是有些不同之处的\NThere is a little bit of difference to working with the lead actor that's the director as well
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.24,0:28:41.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,真是有些伤脑经 因为他有想法 他知道怎么做最好\NIt makes a little more nerve-racking,cuz' he got his vision he knows exactly what he wants
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.23,0:28:44.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你不想让他受伤 但又得给他最好的效果\NYou want to keep him safe but you also want to give him what he is looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.37,0:28:49.09,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后你推他 把情势拉回到中立 然后在那一刹那出手 这样画面就很棒了\NAnd then you push,bring it back down to neutral but just that split second it looks great
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.19,0:28:52.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,再往这边来一点 划个圆 -对\NCome here more  A circle -yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.13,0:28:57.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这一场戏我要打Bryan 打Walter White \NThis is the scene where I actually hit Bryan,hit Walter White
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.23,0:28:59.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这是个出其不意的拳头\NWhen he doesn't know that I am actually gonna hit him
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.36,0:29:00.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,开拍\NAction
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.55,0:29:10.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,没事吧 说真的 我不喜欢你那个眼神\NYou OK  I gotta say I don't like the way you are looking at me right now
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.22,0:29:19.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,其实真实打架的情形 \NYou know like most fights are
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.95,0:29:25.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,都不是好莱坞式的纠缠不清的假斗\NIt doesn't go on and on and on,fake Hollywood style,slugging and slugging
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.89,0:29:30.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而是一个拳头下去 应声倒地 然后就完事了 又快又狠\NIt's usually one hit and boom  then it's over,it's violent and quick'
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.33,0:29:35.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是你这个混蛋 你撞车不让我去洗衣厂\NYou you drove into traffic to keep me away from that laundry
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.09,0:29:40.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,打电话骗我Marie受伤住院 \NThat call I got from Marie said she was in the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.52,0:29:46.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不是Pinkman搞的鬼 你有我手机号码\NThat wasn't Pinkman. You had my cell
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.46,0:29:53.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我很惊喜在表演中看到了Hank的痛苦\NI was so happily surprised that pain that comes out in hank's expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.13,0:29:57.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他因为被背叛的愤怒以及煎熬\NHis demeanor he is angry as hell,he is betrayed. He is in agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.67,0:30:01.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你居然杀了十个证人 炸了养老院\NYou killed ten witnesses,you bombed a nursing home.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.29,0:30:08.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他不打算打我了 但他抓着我的头\NHe is not gonna hit me again,but he is like,he grabs the hold of my head
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.29,0:30:15.41,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因痛苦而颤抖 真是令人心碎\NVibrating with this anguish,oh  it's just really heartbreaking
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.50,0:30:26.53,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你要是真的不知道我是谁 那你最好小心点\NIf you don't know who I am,then maybe your best course is to tread lightly
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.81,0:30:35.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡\NCut it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.96,0:30:56.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第五季 第十集 《地面之下》\N导演:Michelle Maclaren 编剧:Thomas Schanauz
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.56,0:31:13.52,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第五季第十集 我们有了一辆制毒巴士 由Mark S Freeborn设计\NS05E10 we got this meth lab bus,mark S freeborn designed it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.63,0:31:18.34,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这里是第五季上部分里Todd带来的设备\NThis is the equipment from the first half of season 5,that Todd took
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.44,0:31:24.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,用的正是Vamonos杀虫公司用的移动装备\NRight this is the same equipment that we use in the mobile Vamonos pest control set up
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.40,0:31:29.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们和Todd做了交易就把这个带走了 Walt脱离了这个业务\NThey made a deal with Todd,so they went and Walt bailed from the business
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.82,0:31:35.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFF00&\pos(315,32)}Hells Angels:地狱天使帮是世界上非同小可的现代犯罪组织
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.82,0:31:35.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Mark像是圣诞老人和狂野凶狠的飞车族的混合体\NMark is mix between Santa Clause and{\c&HFFFF00&} hells angels biker
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.34,0:31:39.85,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在一大群幕前幕后工作人员中 \NIn a show populated by characters in front of and behind the lens
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.94,0:31:43.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他是出类拔萃的一个\NMark is a character par excellence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.11,0:31:50.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,很多道具化学品都可以用厨房搅拌机制作\NLot of the elements are found,you can use a kitchen mixer to mix chemicals
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.27,0:31:54.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所有的东西都必须能通过 我们面前这个30英寸的舱门\NEverything has to fit through the a 30 inch hole where the trap door is in front of us
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.10,0:32:03.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,整体的效果是为了把凸显这里的阴暗 险恶 肮脏 令人不适\NThe overall effect is to create a sinister,shadowy,uncomfortable,unsanitary environment
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.11,0:32:10.21,2,NTP,0,0,0,,与Walt和Jesse的 卫生又安全的大实验室形成对比\NCompared to Walt and Jesse's very sanitary,very safe,very clean meth lab
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.31,0:32:13.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不可思议 他们做了很细节的东西 所有的窗户都必须是树脂玻璃的\NIt's fantastic,he has done the details,all the windows has to be plexi
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.24,0:32:16.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们在窗户上做涂鸦 \NUh..what they have done is they did graffiti on the windows
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.05,0:32:20.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在树脂玻璃后面铺上灰尘\NSo we have the dirt,is held in the plexi behind the window..
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.09,0:32:21.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们准备好了吗\NAre they ready for me or not
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.08,0:32:28.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Laura 开拍后 我会指示灰尘落下来 \NSo laura,I am gonna say on action,I'm gonna cue the dirt to come down,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.24,0:32:33.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我会模拟子弹的声音 我们估计要做好几次\NThen I gonna say bullet all right  then we will probably do that a couple of times
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.62,0:32:40.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Michelle拍的动作戏是我见过最好的\NMichelle Maclaren directs action better than anyone I have worked with
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.26,0:32:46.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她第一次看剧本的时候 这段画外的枪战场景快把她逼疯了\NThis shoot-out happens off camera,and that kind of drove Michelle crazy when she read it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.86,0:32:48.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,为什么不把枪战拍出来 她说\NShe said,why can we see shootout
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.74,0:32:51.26,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我说 这场戏不能这样拍 \NI said cuz' that's not the way we want to do this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.34,0:32:54.26,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为这段我们想用Lydia的视角来叙事\NWe want to play this through the point of view Lydia Rodarte-Quayle
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.35,0:32:56.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她在地下 而枪战在她头顶上发生\NAs she heard the gunfire going on above her
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.95,0:32:58.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她说 能不能就拍一点点 \NShe says,yeah can we see a little bit of it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.62,0:33:01.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,可以剪掉其他的... 就拍一丁点点...\NCan we cut away the...just a little ...can we see a little little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.75,0:33:03.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我说 不行...\NAnd I say no..
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.39,0:33:07.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,扔弹壳 梆梆\NShell  Bang bang
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.97,0:33:10.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我最喜欢Michelle的一点就是\NOne of the many things I love about Michelle is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.19,0:33:11.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就算她尽力控制自己  \NEven when she is reined in,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.26,0:33:17.16,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她还是会对那些戏份精益求精 亮出狮吼功\NShe would still find a way to milk those moments and hit those high notes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.26,0:33:18.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,落尘土\NDirt
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.82,0:33:22.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,低下头 警惕地抬起头 看着弹壳\NPut your head down,look up alert,look at the shell
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.00,0:33:25.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,梆\NBang
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.30,0:33:27.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们并不是在真的巴士上 我们是在一个舞台上\NWe weren't on a bus,we were on a stage
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.93,0:33:30.44,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而且头顶也没有一场真实的枪战\NAnd there was not really a shoot-out up above
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.52,0:33:32.97,2,NTP,0,0,0,,演员们则是孤身一人身处场景之中\NBut the actor is in the scene by themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.07,0:33:36.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以你会想要帮助她们创造一个利于发挥的背景\NAnd you want to help create the setting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.37,0:33:41.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,总不能毫无生气地说灰尘 子弹 邦邦邦吧\NYou don't wanna go dirt,bullets,bang bang bang
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.23,0:33:42.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为那样对演员发挥很不好\NCuz it's not very good for the actors
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.95,0:33:47.52,2,NTP,0,0,0,,看子弹 低下头 邦邦邦\Nlook to the bullets,look to the bullets,and head down,bang bang bang
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.99,0:33:50.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,看舱口	\NAnd hatch
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.61,0:33:55.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我会完全投入其中 大叫着邦邦邦 因为那就是正在发生的啊\NSo I get in to into it,I was like bang bang bang,that's what's happening up there
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.23,0:34:00.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡 很棒 你们真不错 多谢大家 非常好\NCut it,good stuff,thank you guys that's great
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.95,0:34:05.66,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Laura 你可以回家好好泡个脚舒缓一下了\NLaura,you can go home and soak your feet
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.76,0:34:09.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,能上这个剧 我真的有点战战兢兢的\NI was really intimidated to come on
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.99,0:34:15.44,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但又非常高兴能得到一个如此棒的角色\NBut at the same time,so delighted to get such an amazing part
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.54,0:34:18.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所幸的是 我能全身心投入其中\NLuckily I just dive into that character
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.84,0:34:25.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,本集 Laura的部分结束\NEpisode wrap-up on laura
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.88,0:34:30.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,虽然这个布景只用上两分半钟\NDespite the fact that the set has been on camera for a grand total of two and a half minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.35,0:34:33.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是这是链条上不可或缺的一环 使得故事顺利的被讲述\NIt's a link in a chain,it tells a story
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.37,0:34:38.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而一个好故事一定是完整的链条\NAnd the best story-telling is what completes a chain
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.36,0:34:43.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,两分半上镜时间确实少 谁在乎呢 每一秒都值得\NSo two and a half minutes of screen time,who cares,it's worth every second
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.04,0:34:52.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,好了伙计们 第一场要开始了 安静点\NOK guys first scene is in,lets get quiet please
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.42,0:34:57.89,2,NTP,0,0,0,,人们喜欢谈论《绝命毒师》中那些大场面\NPeople talk about the big moments on Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.98,0:34:59.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是值得讨论的是 这部剧的灵魂和精髓\NBut it could be argued that the heart of the show
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.87,0:35:02.21,2,NTP,0,0,0,,则存在于那些安静的时刻 \NIs the quieter moments
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.27,0:35:07.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,比如老白在浴室地板上不省人事那场戏\NLike the moment in which Walt passed out on the floor of his bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.30,0:35:09.69,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这些角色的安静时刻\NThese very quiet moments of character
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.78,0:35:14.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,会让我们真正的阐释和理解这些角色 明白他们的信仰\NWhere we illuminate and understand who these characters really are and what they really believe
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.94,0:35:17.73,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那才是本剧的灵魂所在\NAre the heart and soul of the show
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.55,0:35:24.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Anna Gunn是这样一个超棒的演员\NAnna Gunn was just a terrific actor to work with
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.58,0:35:30.51,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们之间形成了一个非常亲密的关系 滋养了深厚的友谊\NWe developed a very close relationship and friendship with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.60,0:35:34.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,以及信任 我们知道 我们会关照对方保护对方\NAnd a trust we knew we would gonna watch each other and protect each other
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.79,0:35:39.27,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不仅仅是作为演员 更是作为镜头之外的平凡人\NAs actors and as people,in a scene and outside the scene
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.27,0:35:42.00,2,NTP,0,0,0,,开拍\NAction
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.62,0:35:52.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,天 我昏了多久了 \NOh god how long was I out
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.91,0:35:55.85,2,NTP,0,0,0,,四五个钟头吧\NAbout for 4 or 5 hours
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.97,0:35:59.62,2,NTP,0,0,0,,故事开头 Skyler是整个剧的道德中心\NSkyler started out as the moral center of the show
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.71,0:36:03.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她质问别人 慢着 你在干嘛 你不能这么做\NAnd the person saying Wait a sec,what are you doing,you can't do that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.83,0:36:06.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而这让观众不开心了\NAnd that made the audience angry
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.28,0:36:08.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这样你高兴了吗\NDoes that make you happy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.68,0:36:13.53,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我不记得上次我高兴是什么时候了\NI can't remember last time when I was happy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.61,0:36:16.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有人说 我恨她 她是个贱人\NWhen somebody says,I hate her,she is a bitch
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.62,0:36:20.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我会想 等等 你为什么会这么想呢 难道你不明白吗 \NI think,wait a second,why do you think that,don't you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.46,0:36:22.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你不能理解她所经历的痛苦吗 \NDon't you understand what she is going through
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.27,0:36:24.75,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我本人会很受伤\NAnd I take it very very personally
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.82,0:36:27.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会发现在每一部剧中 \NWhat we figured out is that in every show
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.69,0:36:30.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,都有一个主人公和一个反派\NThere's a protagonist and there's a antagonist
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.30,0:36:35.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,本剧主人公就是老白 但是他却是一个反英雄式的角色\NIn the show the protagonist is Bryan,but he is an anti-hero
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.35,0:36:39.09,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他做了很多坏事\NHe is a guy who's doing pretty bad things
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.36,0:36:47.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Vince从未想过让我演个哭哭啼啼的软弱女人\NVince never ever wanted some soft,hand-wringing,weeping woman
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.28,0:36:51.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在前几季如果我偶尔泪眼汪汪\NIf I got teary in the first couple of seasons
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.56,0:36:54.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他会明确地对我说 不能那样\NHe specifically would say to me,don't do that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.17,0:37:01.03,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他想让她成为钢铁般无坚不摧的女强人\NHe wanted her to be steely,really really strong
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.14,0:37:03.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,从一开始就是一个顶梁柱般的强大的人\NAnd a back-bone of steel from the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.97,0:37:07.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他对于这一点的要求相当明确\NAnd he was extremely specific about that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.50,0:37:11.52,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你不交出这笔钱 就不能自首\NYou can't give yourself up without giving up the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.62,0:37:14.04,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就是这么回事\NThat's the way it works
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.19,0:37:23.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们最好的对策 就是保持沉默\NSo maybe our best move here,is to just keep quiet
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.13,0:37:26.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡 很好\NCut it very nice,check it up please
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.48,0:37:29.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个场景之所以那么有力的原因之一就是\NOne of the reasons why this moment is so powerful is because
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.00,0:37:36.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,编剧们对于Skyler这一角色的塑造和挖掘是一以贯之的\NThe writers have been so consistent with the characterization of Skyler throughout the series
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.10,0:37:39.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而Anna勇于坚持这一点\NAnna has been brave enough to stay the course
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.43,0:37:45.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Anna是个非常出色的演员 因为她勇于保持Skyler这个角色的一致性\NAnna is a very brilliant actor since she is very brave for staying true to Skyler
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.75,0:37:56.00,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第五季 第十一集 《供认》\N导演:Michael Slovis 编剧: Gennifer Hutchson
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.48,0:38:00.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Michael Slovis执导了第五季第十一集 \NMichael Slovis directed 511
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.32,0:38:04.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,对于他的执导方式 我非常热爱的有两点\NThere are two things I really love about the way he approaches directing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.35,0:38:07.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,首先是他对于表演的重视\NOne of them is his emphasis on performance
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.66,0:38:25.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,看着Michael在片场和演员们深入探讨是个非常棒的事情\NWatching Michael come alive when he is dealing with the actors is a wonderful thing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.49,0:38:26.89,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他的指导就是那画龙点睛的一笔\NHe is that magical touch
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.21,0:38:28.74,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就好像这样 我脑子都乱了\NWhen it's like what a fucking thing I'm thinking..
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.83,0:38:29.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就是那样\NExactly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.33,0:38:35.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他会问我话 但是我不啥都想说\NHe is gonna ask me and I don't wanna say
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.75,0:38:39.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,应该是对于我来说最难的一场戏了吧 \NOne of our hardest scene for me,a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.33,0:38:41.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,一般情况我都能很快搞定\NUsually I get it right away
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.58,0:38:44.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-这场戏的动作和音量很微妙\N-small movements,speak volumes in a scene like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.48,0:38:49.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,确实有点难以把握\NThat's why,you know,it can be kinda tricky to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.30,0:38:52.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我跟她的互动是什么样一种程度  你理解我什么意思吗\NYou know how much am I gonna engage with her,you know what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.36,0:38:56.68,2,NTP,0,0,0,,她脆弱的坐着 而你强势的站着 就要这样一种感觉\NTo something really nice about her down,you up
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.77,0:39:02.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就好像她是如此渺小\NLike she is looking very so small you know
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.38,0:39:04.74,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我现在就觉得挺无力渺小的\NI'm feeling pretty small right now
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.79,0:39:07.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我好的感情戏都是和Betsy一起拍的\NAll my emotional good scenes are always with Betsy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.09,0:39:10.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,说真的 跟你一起拍戏很舒坦\NSo it's very comforting,seriously,by the way
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.52,0:39:17.27,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有你陪伴我走过这个拍摄的旅程真好\NIt's really been nice to have you as the person to get through the stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.37,0:39:22.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我总是跟Dean说能够演他的荧屏伴侣是我的荣幸\NI always told Dean that it's my privilege and honor to play his television wife
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.21,0:39:26.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,现在 我和Betsy都没看过Walt的自首视频\NSo neither Betsy nor I have seen the Walt confession
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.13,0:39:29.66,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们故意这样做的 决定提前不看\NWe kinda made a choice,we wanted to see it for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.76,0:39:31.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这样的话他们在拍的时候\NWhen they actually film us watching it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.90,0:39:36.75,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就能给出第一次看的反应了\NSo we can have a reaction to it,for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.90,0:39:47.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,机位就绪 -机位就绪\NSet -set
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.21,0:39:51.84,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我叫Walter Hartwell White\NMy name is Walter Hartwell white
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.95,0:39:55.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我住在新墨西哥州阿尔伯克基\NI live at 308 Negra arroyo lane,Albuquerque,New Mexico,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.49,0:40:00.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,以下是我的坦白\NThis is my confession
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.44,0:40:03.75,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如果你正在看这个录像\NIf you're watching this tape
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.65,0:40:06.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我可能已经死了\NI'm probably dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.66,0:40:10.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,被我的连襟Hank Schrader谋杀的\NMurdered by my brother-in-law,Hank Schrader.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.22,0:40:14.62,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你觉得他把这个给谁看了 \NWho do you think he's shown this to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.38,0:40:18.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,没人 这是个威胁 \NNo one.it's a threat
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.43,0:40:23.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我再步步紧逼的话 他就要这样做了\NIt's what he will do if I don't back off
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.07,0:40:29.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我觉得你应该把这个给Ramey看\NI think you should show this to Ramey
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.36,0:40:31.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,趁着还来得及\NJust get ahead of it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.61,0:40:35.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个录像就是一堆谎言\NThat video is a bunch of lies,hank
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.44,0:40:37.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,任何了解你的人都能看出来啊\NAnybody who knows you will know
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.45,0:40:44.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道 我又不傻 十七万七千 \NI know,I'm not morons $177,000
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.56,0:40:49.41,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他在胡说些什么 Marie \NWhat the hell's he talking about  Marie
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.56,0:40:51.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡\NCut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.81,0:40:54.52,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你们演的精彩极了\NThat was beyond wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.62,0:40:57.90,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个场景非常复杂 感情波动很大\NIt's complicated scene with a lot of hills and valleys
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.14,0:41:02.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这些演员都是一流的\NThese guys were just wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.78,0:41:05.90,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你基本上可以说是最平易近人的工作伙伴了 -是啊 我还最棒的\NBasically you are just the easiest person to work with,-yeah,and best
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.99,0:41:08.33,2,NTP,0,0,0,,最有才的 -那当然啦 绝对的\NAnd the most gifted. -yeah,absolutely
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.45,0:41:11.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,神呐 他真会说谎\NGod,he's such a fucking liar man
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.77,0:41:20.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,开拍\NAction
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.94,0:41:26.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Schrader探员 最近是不是又对哪个嫌犯用刑了 \NAgent schrader.beat any good suspects lately
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.45,0:41:27.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,嘿 高个子和那个更高的\NHey,tall and taller
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.37,0:41:29.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,问问他他和我的客户有什么过节\NAsk him his history with my client
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.11,0:41:31.67,2,NTP,0,0,0,,上次他俩单独待一起的的时候 他把这个可怜的小伙子打到神志不清了\NLast time they were alone together he knocked the poor kid unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.40,0:41:33.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以是要怎样 \NSo what's it gonna be
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.64,0:41:36.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,想把这事搞成像蒙大拿那么大的民权诉讼吗 那样的话乐意为你们效劳\NA civil rights lawsuit the size of Montana,'cause I'll oblige you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.32,0:41:41.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我对剧组的邀请毫无防备\NI was really blindsided by the invitation to be a part of the show
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.47,0:41:44.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,非常意外 我完全没预料到\NIt was a shock,a surprise,something I never saw coming
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.88,0:41:46.69,2,NTP,0,0,0,,再见了 拳王 护住您的左翼\NOh,so long,Rocky.keep your left up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.78,0:41:49.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,警探们 请您们先行离开\NDetectives,I'm inviting you to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.33,0:41:54.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,第二季的时候我只演了三集  第三季的十三集中我有十集戏份\NIn season 2 I was in 3 episodes,and in season 3 I was in 10 of 13
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.12,0:41:56.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至到那时候 我也没看过这部剧\NAnd I still hadn't seen the show,even then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.98,0:41:59.16,2,NTP,0,0,0,,像我刚说的 我就没从头看过这部剧\NLike I said I didn't watch it from the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.26,0:42:03.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以在我参与的第二季 也就是你们看到的第三季\NSo in that second season that I did and third season that you see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.66,0:42:07.31,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我不是很清楚剧情到底发生了什么 \NI didn't know entirely what was going on
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.43,0:42:10.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,或者我谈论的是哪个人 在我演独角戏的时候\NOr who I was talking about when I do some of the monologues
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.83,0:42:15.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,特别是当我提到Gus 和其他没有对手戏的角色\NEspecially when I came to Gus and other characters who are offscreen from me
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.24,0:42:17.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那些没有对手戏但又确实认识的角色的时候\NWho I never interacted but I knew about
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.33,0:42:22.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以有时候Bryan会看着我 因为我重音没搞对\NSo Bryan would look at me sometimes cuz I would have the wrong emphasis
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.13,0:42:24.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,或者我错误地表达了某些事情\NOr say something in the wrong way
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.17,0:42:30.97,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他就会说Gus就是那个和我合作的那个人 你是认识他的\NHe'd be like Gus is the guy that I'm working with,you know him
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.05,0:42:35.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他还会做出这样的表情 说你根本没看过这部剧 是不是\NAnd he will go like this,you haven't watched the show,have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.39,0:42:40.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后我就会这样 哈哈哈 但从来没正面回答过\NAnd I go,haha-ah...and I've never answered him
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.04,0:42:45.82,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你可以帮我一个忙吗 告诉我你到底怎么了\NBut will you do me a favor and tell me what is exactly up with you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.91,0:42:47.82,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我让我的人拼死拼活\NI got my guys busting their asses
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.92,0:42:50.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,想把Walt的钱给藏起来 不让条子发现\NTrying to hide Walt's money from the feds
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.37,0:42:51.70,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你却把你的钱往窗外撒\NAnd you're tossing yours out of a window
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.79,0:42:53.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而我还得从新闻上知道你的雷锋事迹\NAnd I have to hear about it on the news
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.29,0:42:58.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,喜剧的某些方面很难   好的喜剧很难\NCertain aspects of comedy are hard,and good comedy is hard
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.93,0:43:05.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,需要努力 但我觉得演好这个简直更难\NTake some effort,but I feel like this is harder by a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.54,0:43:09.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我搞砸了 我没说错吧 我搞砸了三次 \NI fucked up,am I kidding  fucked up 3 times
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.27,0:43:13.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我后退太远 还是因为 我没把镜头转过去  \NI stepped back too far  or I didn't turn the camera
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.82,0:43:15.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我还编了自己的台词 -是的\NAnd I made up my own lines -right
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.94,0:43:18.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但这是个问题吗 在《绝命毒师》剧组\NBut is that a problem here on Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.26,0:43:21.58,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们喜欢NG吗 能容忍一点吗\NDo they like that or not like that yes or no,a little or a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.67,0:43:23.16,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们可不喜欢NG 非常不喜欢\NNot even a little
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.33,0:43:26.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我有时候会觉得 他不认为他值得演这个角色\NI sometime got the feeling he does not feel like he deserves this character
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.92,0:43:30.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但其实 他绝对值得演Saul Goodman\NAnd he absolutely does deserve to play Saul Goodman
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.33,0:43:33.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为你知道他很有趣 事实就是这样\NBecause you know he's funny,and he is,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.82,0:43:38.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但他没意识到他已经成为一个多么出色的演员 \NBut when he doesn't seem to realize what a fine dramatic actor he has become
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.51,0:43:40.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他现在是 一直都是\NHe is and always was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.89,0:43:42.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-你会演好的 你会演好的 -那要到什么时候\N-you'll get it you'll get it -at what point
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.00,0:43:46.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-第八条吧 -我看是第八季吧\NBy the end of the 8th -by 8th season
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.14,0:43:48.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-哎呀 你会没问题的\N-yeah,you'll be cool
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.27,0:43:50.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,哦 该我了吗 要进去了 太好了\NOh me I gotta be in here that'll be great
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.95,0:43:52.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Odenkirk,别再搞砸了 好吗\NSo Odenkirk,don't fuck up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.03,0:43:54.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,好的 你说对了\NYeah,exactly right
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.19,0:44:02.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Michael Slovis还有一件很擅长的事 就是选景\NThe other thing that Michael Slovis does so well is the way he choose his locations
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.25,0:44:07.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你能从第五季第十一集看出来 Saul,Walt和Jesse见面的那片穹丘\NYou can see it in 511,the domes where Saul,Walt and Jesse meet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.91,0:44:13.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Vince常说他希望《绝命毒师》看起来像个西部片\NVince always said he always saw Breaking Bad to be kind of like a western
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.12,0:44:15.63,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当我们在沙漠腹地拍摄的时候\NWhen we were shooting in the middle of the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.72,0:44:18.62,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有时候的确像是在拍西部片\NIt does feel like we are shooting a western at times
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.75,0:44:26.18,2,NTP,0,0,0,,今天我们在帕哈里多穹丘 很冷 现在可能只有3度\NToday,we are at the Pajarito domes,it's freezing it's probably 3 degrees right now
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.29,0:44:29.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在拍Walt,Jesse和Saul在沙漠见面的戏份\NWe are shooting Walt Jesse and Saul in the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.89,0:44:33.16,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个场景里 Walt建议Jesse离开Albuquerque\NThis is a big scene where Walt comes suggest Jesse to leave Albuquerque
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.27,0:44:40.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Saul知道一个人 他的专长就是给人新的身份\NSaul knows a man,he specializes in giving people new identities
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.27,0:44:46.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他会帮你搬去很远的地方 为你建立一个新的生活\NHe would move you some places far away,set you up with a whole new life
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.47,0:44:51.21,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在很多荒凉的地方拍摄过\NThere are just so many lonely,desolate places that we shoot
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.32,0:44:56.27,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那些地方 有时候是就是角色们感情的缩影\NThat just are the mere image of how these characters feel at times
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.37,0:44:58.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就是很孤单 寂寞\NIt's just so alone and desolate
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.89,0:45:07.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你就直说要我帮你好了 直说你根本不在乎我的死活\NJust ask me for a favor,and tell me you don't give a shit about me
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.54,0:45:14.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,告诉我 不这样做的话你就会杀了我 像你杀死Mike那样\NIt's either this or you kill me the same way you killed mike
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.98,0:45:20.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我喜欢演一个跟我自己不一样的人\NI feel most comfortable playing someone that I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.09,0:45:24.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,站在人堆面前 公众讲话会让我很害怕\NI got terrified doing public speaking,standing in front of crowds
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.29,0:45:29.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是在镜头面前 只要是演跟我完全相反的人\NBut in front of camera,as long as it's someone completely polar opposite of me
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.06,0:45:32.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我就会完全放松\NThat's when I feel most comfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.61,0:45:38.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不就是这样吗 特地赶到这样荒无人烟的地方 \NIsn't that what  this is all about  meeting way to hell out here
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.64,0:45:42.68,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就是以防我拒绝 \NJust in case I say no
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.78,0:45:45.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当你看见Aaron和Bryan一起的时候\NWhen you look at Aaron and Bryan together
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.69,0:45:49.26,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你就好像看到那种 良师益友的关系\NYou can really see the sort of a mentor kind of situation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.36,0:45:53.29,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Aaron在与Bryan相处的时间里成长为一个更好的演员\NWhere Aaron has only become a better actor for his time spent with Bryan
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.40,0:45:56.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan Cranston的提升空间就没多少了\NThere's very little room for improvement with Bryan Cranston
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.40,0:45:59.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但我认为 在和Aaron一起拍戏时 他意识到自己必须保持最佳状态\NBut I think he's realized he has to be at the top of his game around Aaron
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.97,0:46:01.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这种良好的关系是相互的\NThese two guys are good for one and another
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.81,0:46:12.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡 演得太好了\NCut it -cutting -beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.05,0:46:21.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,为最终集Jack团伙的围场选址
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.83,0:46:25.89,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道 整部剧将在这个特别的地方结束\NI knew the entire series was gonna end at this particular location
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.00,0:46:29.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,把这个地方定好非常的重要\NThis is a very important location to nail down and get right
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.92,0:46:34.06,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们从编剧们那里知道 我们必须找到这个院子\NWe knew from the writers that we had to find this compound
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.18,0:46:36.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,它在最终集之前会有亮相\NAnd we are introducing it in an earlier episode
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.70,0:46:39.27,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是这儿将在大结局里扮演非常重要的角色\NBut that was gonna play a big part in the finale
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.34,0:46:41.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,本来是有点挑战性的\NIt was little bit challenging
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.05,0:46:45.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是因为神的帮助 或者说因为毒师神的帮助\NBut by the grace of god,or the Breaking Bad gods
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.90,0:46:48.75,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们找到了这个完美的地方\NWe just ran into this perfect setting
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.86,0:46:51.47,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是个老旧的铸模工厂\NWhich was an old molding plant
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.57,0:46:55.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这里将上演一场好戏 当我们把一切都弄好了之后\NQuite a lot is gonna happen here,by the time we are set and done
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.60,0:46:59.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如果这是我们最终拍摄的地方的话 我认为是的 非常可能\NIf this is indeed the place we shoot,and I think it will be,probably
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.27,0:47:01.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们想这个桶形建筑\NWe are thinking this barrel shape building here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.91,0:47:03.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,很有可能将成为Todd的制毒室\NIs probably gonna be Todd's meth lab
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.88,0:47:06.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这儿两面都有大型的货车门\NIt's got its giant truck doors on both sides
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.88,0:47:10.38,2,NTP,0,0,0,,里面看上去很不错 然后这边的棕色的砖坯房\NIt looks great inside,and then this brown adobe building
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.47,0:47:12.89,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就在我们面前 磨坊前面\NStraight ahead of us here in front of the big mill building
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.99,0:47:15.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,很有可能将成为Jack的俱乐部\NIs probably gonna be uncle jack's clubhouse
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.60,0:47:17.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,按照我们原先设想的\NOriginally as conceived
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.24,0:47:23.13,2,NTP,0,0,0,,俱乐部 实验室 关押Jesse的地方\NThe club house,the lab,the place where Jesse contained in
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.24,0:47:24.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是整个一个大房间\NWere all one big room
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.01,0:47:28.02,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 现在我们看到这么多可以用的建筑\NAnd we've seen now we had all these buildings to play
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.13,0:47:31.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,还有这个吓人的坑\NAnd this fantastic horrifying pit
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.38,0:47:37.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 我和我的团队找到了这个超赞的地方\NSo my crew and I we found this marvelous location
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.97,0:47:43.39,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我和我的编剧们 要把Jesse带到这里\NI'm gonna bring Jesse here,my writers and i
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.48,0:47:47.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我也很确定 最后我们将帮他逃出这里\NAnd I'm pretty sure at the end of all,we're gonna get him out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.51,0:47:54.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,可以看出 他更担心他 但我不认为除了这样他还能怎样  \Nlook you see that,he's more concerned about him but I don't think he can be more this
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.12,0:47:56.27,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我明白 -你觉得怎么样 \NI got you -what do you think
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.40,0:47:59.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,对吧  -对 不错 -即使他像是..对 正是这样\NRight -I think it's good -even though he's like..yeah...exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.30,0:48:02.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,今天是特别兴奋的一天 因为今天是Sam Catlin\NToday is an incredibly exiting day,because it is sam catlin
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.67,0:48:06.61,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的编剧兼导演 第一次导演\NOur writer and director's,first day directing ever
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:09.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,让他感觉到 我会这么做的\NGive him a little something like I'm gonna do it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.37,0:48:15.05,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我想给毒师剧组的人机会\NI wanna give people opportunities on Breaking Bad
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.17,0:48:16.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,去成长 学习 尝试新事情\NTo grow and learn and do new things
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.03,0:48:20.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个剧的编剧想要执导 第一个要跨越的障碍就是\NHurdle no.1 to get the job of directing on the show as a writer
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.62,0:48:26.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,必须要有激情 过来问我要执导的机会\NWas to have the enthusiasm,require to do it and come to me and ask
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.48,0:48:29.78,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我从没有开诚布公地说 他们可以过来找我\NI did not make it publicly known that they would come to me
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.88,0:48:33.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我希望他们是发自内心地想执导\NI want them to do it because they really wanted to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.23,0:48:35.78,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而不是听说有别的编剧想导演就去跟风\NNot because I heard other writers want to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.21,0:48:38.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是那样吗 \NIs that it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.87,0:48:42.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你想看一眼吗 \NYou wanna take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.75,0:48:45.08,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那样行吗 \NDoes that work
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.87,0:48:49.99,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你希望一直到结束都保持着紧张是吗 \NYou want me to keep that tension all the way
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.11,0:48:54.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-是 你明白他会这样做的 会出事的 -从头到尾一直紧张\N-yeah you do know he's gonna do it,this is happening -all the way to the end all the way to the end
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.88,0:48:57.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Aaron 洒点水到这里 我们开始吧\NAaron flashing water on this,let's roll
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.71,0:49:01.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管我对这个想法不是特别有热情 \NThough I wasn't wild keen on the idea just because
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.67,0:49:04.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为我需要他们和我一起待在编剧室里 但我就是不能拒绝他们\NI need them in the writers room with me,I just couldn't say no
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.02,0:49:08.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 他们想做 他们值得拥有这个权利 他们也争取到了\NBecause they wanted it,they deserved it and they earned
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.22,0:49:13.34,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有时作为负责人你就是得让他们遵循自己的内心\NAnd sometimes as show runner you just gotta let people follow their hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.44,0:49:15.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,去做他们认为重要的事\NAnd do things that are important to them
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.47,0:49:19.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我有当导演的各种优势 因为这集剧本是我写的\NI had all these advantages coming in because I wrote the episode
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.56,0:49:24.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我知道这部剧的基调 我也了解这些演员 知道他们的才华所在\NI know the tone of the show,and I personally know actors and their talents
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.51,0:49:27.47,2,NTP,0,0,0,,于是我可以就着他们的基础来拍\NSo it was just like I was sort of starting on their base
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.56,0:49:29.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Jesse 把打火机放下\NJesse put down that lighter
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.54,0:49:36.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他向一个小孩下毒 一个八岁的男孩\NHe poisoned a little kid,an 8 year old boy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.92,0:49:42.08,2,NTP,0,0,0,,只是因为 这是一步棋\NJust because,you know,just as a move
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.19,0:49:46.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Walt是个混蛋 我知道了 我们会谈的\NWalt's bastard secret's out,we'll talk about it
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.96,0:49:49.48,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡 表演得很棒\NCut,that's beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.57,0:49:55.48,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Sam以前是演员 我知道他会和这些演员合作得很好\NSam used to be an actor,and I knew sam would be great working with the actors
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.59,0:50:00.50,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他来到那里的时候很自信 有备而来 知道自己想要的是什么\NHe came there confident,prepared,knew exactly what he wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.60,0:50:03.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不会试着画蛇添足\NDidn't try to do more than what needed to be done
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.31,0:50:05.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他的工作完成得很漂亮\NAnd he did a beautiful job
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.04,0:50:21.88,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我大学的时候 认识一个年轻人 名叫Takehiko Kitosara\NWhen I was in college,I knew a young man named Takehito Kitosara
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.99,0:50:24.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,30)\c&HFFFF00&}CP：Cerebral Palsy 脑瘫
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.99,0:50:24.81,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他患有脑瘫\NHe had {\c&HFFFF00&}CP
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.94,0:50:27.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,挺严重的\NHe was afflicted with it pretty severely
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.54,0:50:31.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他需要手杖走路 跟Walt Jr.一样\NHe needed crutches to walk,as does Walt Jr.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.34,0:50:35.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我跟他很熟 他是个很好的人\NAnd I got to know him very well,he was a wonderful person
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.21,0:50:40.34,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他属于那种人 你的生命会因为结识他们而变得更加富足\NHe was one of people you meet in your life that make you richer for having known them
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.45,0:50:43.21,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他20多岁就去世了\NHe passed away in his mid-20s
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.33,0:50:45.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,毕业后没几年\NNot too many years after college
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.67,0:50:49.43,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我在构思Walt Jr这个角色的时候想到了他\NI was thinking of him when I was thinking of Walt Jr
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.54,0:50:52.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,于是就想到了让Walt Jr也患有脑瘫\NAnd the idea of Walt Jr having cp
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.55,0:51:02.09,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当他写Walt Jr的时候 他脑子里就想到了他的身体顽疾\NWhen he was writing Walt Jr. He had him in mind his physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.21,0:51:06.20,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后我在剧本上看到他这么写的时候\NAnd what it really was when I saw that on on the script
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.30,0:51:09.38,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我就说 哥儿们 写得很精准啊 我能演\NI was like,dude,spot on it,I got this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.50,0:51:18.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-一切都好吗 -好 只是工作上的事\NEverything OK -oh yeah,just work stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.79,0:51:23.77,2,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管那个角色患有脑瘫 我们知道我们不想区别对待他\NEven though the character has cp,we knew we didn't want to treat him any differently
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.88,0:51:28.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,那个角色不会被区别对待 就像RJ 现实生活中不会被区别对待\NThe character differently,just like RJ,not treated any differently in real life
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.42,0:51:33.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如果这有希望能向观众传达一种信息\NAnd that's,hopefully,if that sends a message to the public
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.70,0:51:38.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就是关于如何与残疾人和谐相处\NOf how to integrate with those with apparent disabilities
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.44,0:51:41.85,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为我们算得上做出了一点贡献\NAnd I think we've done a little to help that up
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.01,0:51:47.44,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我爱你伙计 -我也爱你\NI love you buddy -I love you too
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.51,0:51:52.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我是这个星球上最幸运的人 得以和我身旁的这个人一起工作\NI'm the luckiest person on this planet to be able to work with this man
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.43,0:51:56.32,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我还以为你最想和Bob Odenkirk一起合作呢\NI thought it was Bob Odenkirk you really wanted to work with
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.43,0:51:59.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-别耍我了 别骗我了 -事实上 Bob是...\NDon't fool me,don't give me that crap -actually Bob is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.37,0:52:02.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你想和Bob合作 不是我\NYou wanted to work with Bob Odenkirk,not me
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.62,0:52:04.90,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我从十三岁就和你一起合作了\NI've been working with you since I was 13
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.98,0:52:08.22,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-所以说你是烦我咯 -是啊 你得展翅飞翔不是 \NSo you are tired of me -yeah,you know,you got to spread the wings
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.32,0:52:11.92,2,NTP,0,0,0,,鸟儿们最终将离开巢穴\NThe birds have to leave the nest eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.44,0:52:24.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,你就在这里看一眼 然后你就想\NIf you just take one moment here and you'll just be like
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.69,0:52:29.58,2,NTP,0,0,0,,OK 我马上要从最高跳水板上跳下来了 然后就走\NOK,I'm gonna jump off the highest diving board and then go
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.59,0:52:36.65,2,NTP,0,0,0,,挺酷的 我们很少在《绝命毒师》里拍这么亮堂的景\NIt's really cool,we've not really done our Breaking Bad in this sort of white color world
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.76,0:52:39.07,2,NTP,0,0,0,,原来剧本里写的是要在公园里拍\NOriginally this was scripted to be sort of a park
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.18,0:52:42.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而Christian 我们的选址经理 想到了这个点子\NChristian our locations manager came up with an idea of this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.56,0:52:45.00,2,NTP,0,0,0,,一个广场 明显不是公园\NA plaza which obviously isn't a park
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.09,0:52:50.66,2,NTP,0,0,0,,有足够的公开度 很满足我们的需求\NWith the publicness of it really sort of suits our needs
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.22,0:53:00.45,2,NTP,0,0,0,,摄像机对准电话\NCamera right to the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.99,0:53:05.00,2,NTP,0,0,0,,待在那儿 别动\NHold right there,hold
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.58,0:53:10.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们用这个 你看见这个窃听器了吗\NWe use one of these things,you've seen the earwigs
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.19,0:53:12.10,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我把这个放进耳朵里 他耳朵里也有一个\NI put this in my ear,he's got one in his ear
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.20,0:53:14.74,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可以互相听到对方 因为我们还装上了麦\NWe could hear each other because we are miked also
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.81,0:53:17.51,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Aaron在记他的对白\NSo Aaron is going over his dialogues right now
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.58,0:53:19.61,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他在和他的对白挣扎\NHe's been having the toughest time with his dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.70,0:53:24.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,看看这个 只有这个 几句对白而已\Nlook at this,it's only this,a little bit of dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.63,0:53:26.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但我就是做不到啊\NI just can't do it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.04,0:53:31.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他以记住准确的台词为荣\NHe prides himself on getting all these lines exactly right
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.26,0:53:34.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,而我以不记而自豪\NAnd I pride myself on not
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.23,0:53:37.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他把他的台词藏在电话旁边\NHe's stuck his lines up on the telephone
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.83,0:53:41.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-我不会这样做的 -很公平嘛\NI'm not gonna do it now -it's all fair,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.27,0:53:46.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-不不不 我不会这样做的 -没事啊 白兰度就这么做了\NNo,no,I'm not gonna do it -do it.hey Brando did it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.29,0:53:50.53,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-我又不是白兰度 -我是指罗伯特白兰度\NI'm not Brando though -I meant Bob Brando
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.63,0:53:53.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我没这么做啊  大家都看到了啊\NI didn't do it,just so everyone knows
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.70,0:53:55.96,2,NTP,0,0,0,,摄像机在这里 然后你这样看着电话\NThe camera is here and you are looking at the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.03,0:53:59.56,2,NTP,0,0,0,,就把台词藏在那里 不不不 为什么不啊\NJust put the lines up on,no no.. Why not
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.64,0:54:01.78,2,NTP,0,0,0,,等等等等....\NWait wait wait.....
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.69,0:54:08.12,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Allan好了吗 \NAllan
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.20,0:54:10.34,2,NTP,0,0,0,,马上给你接通 就快好了\NHe's gonna get it for you,he's really there
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.39,0:54:16.61,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan在片场的行为都很幼稚\NBryan behaves very immaturely on set
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.70,0:54:20.79,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我这样说已经很给他面子了\NAnd I say that in the nicest way possible
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.87,0:54:21.87,2,NTP,0,0,0,,卡\NCut it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.29,0:54:29.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我这条差点就过了 我勒个去\NI almost had it too,damn it,man
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.33,0:54:32.24,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们演的是一个很紧张很黑暗的故事\NWe are telling a very intense dark story
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.35,0:54:35.71,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是当你没在拍的时候 适当地用幽默来缓和紧张气氛是很好的\NWhen you are not shooting it,it's good to kind of break the tension with humor
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.81,0:54:40.35,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他们在谈Bryan的戏份\NThey are discussing Bryan Cranston's coverage
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.45,0:54:42.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我的已经拍好了\NMy coverage is already done
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.66,0:54:46.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,所以今天最重要的部分已经完成了\NSo really the most important part of the day is finished
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.45,0:54:53.03,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但是现在... -我能听见你哦 我有装备 我知道的\NBut now... -so,I can hear you,I have an accessory,I know
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.10,0:54:54.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,哦 你能听见啊\NOh you can hear me
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.03,0:55:02.19,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-麦克风和窃听器啊\N-the microphone and the earwig
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.26,0:55:05.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-哦 我忘了我们还有这个 麦克风和听筒\NI forgot that we had this,the mics and earpiece
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.24,0:55:11.23,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不过 没关系 他需要听到这些\NWell it's good,he needs to hear that you know
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.32,0:55:16.36,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我可不想让我的台词掩盖你精湛的演技\NWell I don't want my off-camera lines overshadow your on-camera performance
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.44,0:55:18.28,2,NTP,0,0,0,,真的 你可以读 Allan也可以读\NBut really,you could read it or Allan could read it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.36,0:55:20.76,2,NTP,0,0,0,,随便去街上拉一个人过来读也可以 \NReally get someone off the street to read the line,I don't really..
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.83,0:55:23.54,2,NTP,0,0,0,,谁来读 完全没有差别\NReally won't make any difference one way or other
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.63,0:55:25.82,2,NTP,0,0,0,,大家注意了 开拍了\NHere we go guys let's roll
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.13,0:55:30.80,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我喜欢我做的事 我觉得很有趣 当人们在这种放松的状态下\NI love what I do,I have fun,and when people are at ease
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.88,0:55:33.10,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不论是演员们还是工作人员 大家就会更有效率\NWhether it's cast or crew,they work better
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.19,0:55:36.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,更开心了嘛  开心了就会表现得更好\NThey are happier,happier people work better
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.03,0:55:40.53,2,NTP,0,0,0,,让你们说我疯了吧 我决定这次拍不看台词\NCall me crazy but I'm gonna try this take without looking at my lines
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.64,0:55:46.17,2,NTP,0,0,0,,开始了 天哪\NHere it goes oh my god
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.08,0:55:55.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我没预想到《绝命毒师》的片场会这么有趣\NI didn't see that Breaking Bad set would be this funny
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.21,0:55:56.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我都不知道为什么\NI really didn't get it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.05,0:56:00.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我没想到这儿会变得如此有趣\NI didn't know it would gonna be this much fun and this funny a place
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.27,0:56:04.61,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这招厉害啊 混蛋\NNice try,asshole
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.72,0:56:08.27,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Jesse 你在哪里 我就想跟你谈谈\NJesse where are you,I just wanted to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.38,0:56:13.11,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不 我不会做你想做的事了 行吗 混蛋\NNo,I'm not doing anything you want any more,OK,asshole
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.18,0:56:15.63,2,NTP,0,0,0,,冷静一下\NJust calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.73,0:56:20.55,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我冷静的不得了 给你提个醒 我会抓住你的\NI'm super calm,Walt,this is just a heads-up,I'm coming for you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.02,0:56:28.75,2,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我非得指出一个人 那一定是Bryan \NIf I got to point one person,that of course is Bryan Cranston
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.85,0:56:32.62,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Bryan在这一行很久了 他是个专业人士\NAnd Bryan Cranston's been doing this job long enough,he's such a pro
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.72,0:56:36.58,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他去过很多片场 好的坏的 他经历过很多情景 好的坏的\NHe's been on sets,good and bad,he's been in situations,good and bad
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.65,0:56:40.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为 他一路走来做出了很明智的决定\NAnd I think he made a conscious decision along the way
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.09,0:56:43.03,2,NTP,0,0,0,,每个人都能尽我们所能的享受其中的乐趣\NThat everyone is gonna have his as good time as we could have
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.10,0:56:44.48,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们将非常努力地工作\NWe are all gonna work our butts off
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.59,0:56:46.60,2,NTP,0,0,0,,但我们将对彼此非常友善\NBut we could be kind to each other nice to each other
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.68,0:56:48.73,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们可以成为一个幸福的大家庭\NAnd we can be a happy family
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.82,0:56:51.14,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们一起上 如何\NLet's go do this,shall we
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.08,0:57:03.90,2,NTP,0,0,0,,不错哟 -进来一起拍\NNice -bring it in,come on in and shot
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.95,0:57:12.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们将互撒鲜血了啊 准备好了吗\NSo we're gonna throw blood on each other,you ready
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.53,0:57:14.73,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-你先来 -好的\NYou do it first -OK
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.62,0:57:26.38,2,NTP,0,0,0,,全撒上来啊 向我开炮啊\NGet it out,get it all out brother
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.48,0:57:28.89,2,NTP,0,0,0,,别顾虑了 6年了 我们\NLet it go,six years man
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.01,0:57:33.64,2,NTP,0,0,0,,小心哦\NWatch out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.39,0:57:46.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,看上去还可以吗 \NDoes it look OK
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.43,0:58:08.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们明天再来拍\N..continue the coverage tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.80,0:58:10.86,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这样阳光能照射到我们\NThat's gonna put us on the sun-side....
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.90,0:58:16.30,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在To'Hajilee 这是Walt埋钱的地方\NWe are in To'Hajilee,this is the place where Walt had buried his money
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.38,0:58:21.95,2,NTP,0,0,0,,也是拍Walt被抓的地方\NThis is the big moment where Walt is actually arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.01,0:58:23.42,2,NTP,0,0,0,,在他埋钱的地方\NAt the spot where his money is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.50,0:58:25.82,2,NTP,0,0,0,,我们应该把主要场景搭在这边 拍车的地方\NWe should most importantly set it up for our car houses
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.93,0:58:30.46,2,NTP,0,0,0,,然后摄像机也要摇过来拍俯瞰镜头\NBut potentially swing this way and do our down shots this way as well
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.52,0:58:34.75,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当我们知道我们第五季第十三集要拍一场枪战\NWhen we knew we are gonna have this shoot-out in episode 513
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.82,0:58:38.72,2,NTP,0,0,0,,将导致可怜的Hank的牺牲\NThat will ultimately lead to poor hank's demise
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.82,0:58:41.37,2,NTP,0,0,0,,以及可怜的Gomez的牺牲的时候\NAnd poor Gomez's demise as well
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.47,0:58:45.01,2,NTP,0,0,0,,早先我就尽力确保\NVery early on I did my best to ensure that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.09,0:58:47.59,2,NTP,0,0,0,,Michelle能执导这非常特别的一集\NMichelle Maclaren would get to direct that particular episode
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.68,0:58:49.94,2,NTP,0,0,0,,他拿着他的手机和电池\NHe gets his phone and the battery
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.44,0:58:53.57,2,NTP,0,0,0,,找地方藏身\Nlooks for a place to hide
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.66,0:58:56.25,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这个场景拍摄量很大 我们有相当多的演员 \NThere was so much to shoot with so many people
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.32,0:59:00.63,2,NTP,0,0,0,,剧本里老是提到谁看到谁了 还要组织联系各部人员\NAnd there are so much reference to looks and connecting different groups
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.71,0:59:04.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,于是我想 我们最好先徒步勘察整个场景\NAnd so I thought we'd better walk through the entire,all the scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.58,0:59:07.49,2,NTP,0,0,0,,这样大家都能尽快熟悉地形\NSo that everybody has the geography down
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.58,0:59:09.93,2,NTP,0,0,0,,可以了 让他们开拍吧 车停的地方\NAll right now give them the action the car place
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.02,0:59:11.98,2,NTP,0,0,0,,当我看到Gomez出来的时候 对吗\NWhen I see Gomez get out,right
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.07,0:59:14.15,2,NTP,0,0,0,,是当你看见Hank的时候 你就表现出 别来别来\NIt's when you see hank and you are like don't come don't come
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.24,0:59:16.83,2,NTP,0,0,0,,-如果我看见Gomez -对 还有Jesse\NIf I see Gomez.. -you know,Jesse
